# {{PROJECT_NAME}} — Architecture

## Monorepo structure

```
{{PROJECT_NAME}}/
├── packages/
│   ├── frontend/   # React 19 + Vite + Tailwind + Zustand
│   ├── shared/     # Shared TypeScript types and utilities
│   └── backend/    # FastAPI + Pydantic (runs in Docker)
├── docker-compose.yml       # Production
├── docker-compose.dev.yml   # Development (hot reload)
├── turbo.json               # Turborepo pipeline
├── biome.json               # Linting + formatting (TS/JS)
└── pnpm-workspace.yaml      # Workspace config
```

## Package managers
- **pnpm** — JavaScript/TypeScript dependency management and workspace orchestration
- **uv** — Python dependency management (replaces pip/poetry)
- **Turborepo** — Build orchestration across packages

## Docker setup
- Development: `docker-compose.dev.yml` mounts `packages/backend` with hot reload
- Production: `docker-compose.yml` builds from `packages/backend/Dockerfile`
- Python deps install automatically via `uv sync` on container start

## Layer rules
Components (`packages/frontend/src/components/`) must not make API calls directly.
They read from Zustand stores. Stores call the API layer. The API layer owns fetch logic.

This is enforced via TypeScript path aliases — `tsc --noEmit` will fail if a component imports from `@api`.
